venue.fullName: LeRoy A. Ufkes Court at Western Hall

article.headline: Valparaiso 81, Western Illinois 79
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Dan Oppland had 22 points and 10 rebounds and Ali Berdeil added 13 points as Valparaiso beat Western Illinois 81-79 in overtime on Saturday night. Valparaiso (10-9, 7-3 Mid-Continent) made all three of its field goal attempts and hit 6-of-8 free throws in overtime. Oppland, a sophomore, was 12-of-14 from the free throw line as Valparaiso won its sixth straight. Joaquim Gomes added 12 points. Will Lewis made 12-of-13 free throws and led Western Illinois (3-18, 1-8) with 24 points. Bobby Carter added 19 points and three steals for the Leathernecks, who shot 39 percent from the field.
